{"questionId":"9117833","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><strong>Table 1</strong> provides information about Fairland.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><strong>Table 1</strong></p>\n<p><img src=\"__IMG__/a6092d760b91ad7eab33bdf5973fe90c5835223d.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Calculate the unemployment rate in Fairland using <strong>Table 1</strong>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>Unemployment rate = <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{Unemployed}{Labour force}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>U</mi>\n      <mi>n</mi>\n      <mi>e</mi>\n      <mi>m</mi>\n      <mi>p</mi>\n      <mi>l</mi>\n      <mi>o</mi>\n      <mi>y</mi>\n      <mi>e</mi>\n      <mi>d</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>L</mi>\n      <mi>a</mi>\n      <mi>b</mi>\n      <mi>o</mi>\n      <mi>u</mi>\n      <mi>r</mi>\n      <mi>f</mi>\n      <mi>o</mi>\n      <mi>r</mi>\n      <mi>c</mi>\n      <mi>e</mi>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span> × 100 = <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{Labour force-Employed}{Labour force}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>L</mi>\n      <mi>a</mi>\n      <mi>b</mi>\n      <mi>o</mi>\n      <mi>u</mi>\n      <mi>r</mi>\n      <mi>f</mi>\n      <mi>o</mi>\n      <mi>r</mi>\n      <mi>c</mi>\n      <mi>e</mi>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mi>E</mi>\n      <mi>m</mi>\n      <mi>p</mi>\n      <mi>l</mi>\n      <mi>o</mi>\n      <mi>y</mi>\n      <mi>e</mi>\n      <mi>d</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>L</mi>\n      <mi>a</mi>\n      <mi>b</mi>\n      <mi>o</mi>\n      <mi>u</mi>\n      <mi>r</mi>\n      <mi>f</mi>\n      <mi>o</mi>\n      <mi>r</mi>\n      <mi>c</mi>\n      <mi>e</mi>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span> × 100 =&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{0.62&nbsp;× 231&nbsp;− 105}{0.62&nbsp;× 231}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>0.62</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>231</mn>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mn>105</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>0.62</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>231</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp;× 100 = <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{143 − 105}{143}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>143</mn>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mn>105</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mn>143</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp;× 100</p>\n<p><em>Any valid working (such as the correct calculation of the labour force) is sufficient for <strong>[1]</strong></em>.</p>\n<p>= 26.57 % or 26.69 %</p>\n<p>(this depends on when rounding has taken place)</p>\n<p><em>An answer of 26.57 or 26.69 without working is sufficient for <strong>[1]</strong></em>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9117833","referenceCode":"19M.3.HL.TZ0.a","subjectId":"48-dp-economics","title":"Calculate the unemployment rate in Fairland using Table 1.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["First exams 2022","Last exams 2021","Last exams 2021","Section 2: Macroeconomics","First exams 2022","Unit 3: Macroeconomics","3.3 Macroeconomic objectives","3.3.2 Low unemployment","First exams 2022","Unit 3: Macroeconomics","3.3 Macroeconomic objectives","First exams 2022","Unit 3: Macroeconomics","Last exams 2021","Section 2: Macroeconomics","2.3 Macroeconomic objectives","Low unemployment","The meaning of unemployment","Last exams 2021","Section 2: Macroeconomics","2.3 Macroeconomic objectives","Low unemployment","Last exams 2021","Section 2: Macroeconomics","2.3 Macroeconomic objectives"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}